    "recap_headline": "Charlotte",
    "recap_text": "WICHITA, Kan. \u2013\nCharlotte Baseball fell in its first American Conference game of the season on Friday evening (March 20), dropping the series opener at Wichita State, 8-3.\nCharlotte (14-8, 0-1 American) scored first and led by one after four innings but Wichita State (16-8, 1-0 American) rattled off seven unanswered through the fifth and sixth to take control of the game.\nCody Gunderson\nled the Niners with three hits in the game, notching his second three-hit game of the season.\nAlec DeMartino\nwas the only other CLT batter with multiple hits in the game as he had a double and a home run, driving in two of Charlotte's three runs for his seventh multi-RBI game this year.\nDawson Bryce\nkept his team-high hitting streak alive with a single to push it to 15 straight games while\nDylan Koontz\nhad a double for Charlotte's first hit of the game before coming home to score.\nEddie Copper\ngot the start on the mound for the Green and White and fanned five batters in 3.2 innings.\nAJ Camp\nwas charged with the loss in one inning of work before giving way to\nAdam Stanton\n.\nJaden Winter\nfinished out the final three innings of the game with four strikeouts in his longest outing as a Niner.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nCharlotte struck out in order in the first but found a way to get to Wichita's starter in the second, starting the frame off with three straight hits to bring home the first run of the game. Koontz swung at the first pitch of the inning and shot one the other way, just fair inside the third-base line for a double. DeMartino was the next batter up and also put one to the corner in left field, trading places with Koontz to bring him home. Gunderson singled to left in the next at bat to put a pair on before a walk taken by\nAdrian\nJimenez loaded them up, but the Niners couldn't add to their lead.\nWichita State tied things up in the third inning, using a Charlotte error to bring home an unearned run to knot things up at one.\nCharlotte didn't wait long to jump back out in front, loading the bases up again and scoring in the fourth. DeMartino worked a walk and Gunderson singled for the second time to put a pair on. Jimenez drew his second free pass to first with one gone to load them up and Stricklin sent one to the warning track in left, deep enough for a sacrifice fly to plate DeMartino from third.\nThe lead didn't last long as Wichita State plated five runs in the fifth to take a four-run lead, 6-2. The Shockers turned their second double play in as many innings to negate a Niner threat in the next inning, and then tacked on two more in the home half to extend their lead to six through six.\nCharlotte scored its final run of the game, and first since the fourth inning, in the eighth when DeMartino roped one off the scoreboard in left field for his fourth home run of the season.\nUP NEXT\nThe series continues on Saturday (March 21) at 3 p.m. ET before concluding on Sunday at 1 p.m. ET.",
